he Newton and Eden result where Newton ran in 12 tries but only managed to convert one of them. Goal kicking in general was relatively poor and was shared amongst the teams with it not uncommon to see 3 or 4 players used.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 22 June\n| time = 3:45\n| home = North Shore\n| score = 10\u20135\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n  | title = North Shore V City\n  | page = 8\n  | work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLIII| issue=150\n  | date = 1912-06-24\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19120624.2.92\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = City\n| try1 = E Rogers, [[Jim Griffen|Jim Griffin]]\n| con1 = E Rogers, C Clark\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = William Moeki\n| con2 = [[Alex Stanaway]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Devonport Domain\n| attendance =\n| referee = Cunningham\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 22 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Newton\n| score = 38\u20130\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n  | title = Newton V Eden\n  | page = 8\n  | work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLIII| issue=150\n  | date = 1912-06-24\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19120624.2.92\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Eden\n| try1 = Knowles 2, Alan Blakey 2, D Healy 4, Malcolm, Charles Brockliss, Tobin 2\n| con1 = Len Farrant\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Eden Park # 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = R Oliphant\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 22 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 26\u20130\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n  | title = Ponsonby Beats Manukau\n  | page = 8\n  | work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLIII| issue=150\n  | date = 1912-06-24\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19120624.2.92\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>\n| away = Manukau\n| try1 = Horton 2, Matthews, McPherson, Charters, Skeats\n| con1 = Skeats 2\n| pen1 = [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]] 2\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Eden Park # 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = Ma